Summary: Very bright Object in Sky, Was not a star or planet; [cms/tg/pid]
divs: Sighting DetailsGoing to work at 5:10am I saw a bright light in the sky. I don't normally see any star or planet at this location. I took out the binoculars and could see this was not a star but a roundish object. I quickly took out my Nikon S630 digital camera and took several photos. The object was either stationary or slow moving as I could not detect any movement. This object was brighter than any other star or planet in the sky. I was surprised to see it appear as a red color on the top of the object in the photograph.
